cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.HC

The paper discusses the use of machine learning models and neural networks for connectome-based prediction using resting state functional MRI data. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) as the paper uses 3D convolutional neural networks. The paper also involves the use of artificial intelligence (AI) techniques and focuses on the prediction of autism and age, which falls under the category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction).
